---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy - useUtils" 
  description="Learn about our 100% client-side privacy guarantee. We do not transmit, collect, or store any of your private keys or tokens."
  keywords="privacy policy, useutils privacy, local-first privacy, client-side tools security"
>
  <Header />

  <!-- Main Body Content -->
  <main class="flex-grow w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 flex flex-col gap-10">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 pt-2 pb-6 border-b border-border-hairline/60">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50 font-sans">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
        Last updated: June 10, 2026. Your privacy is protected by design: all computations occur entirely inside your browser.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-panel border border-border-hairline rounded-xl p-6 md:p-10 shadow-sm flex flex-col gap-8">
      
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          1. The Local-First Privacy Guarantee
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans pl-4">
          Unlike traditional web utilities that process data on backend servers, <strong class="text-zinc-200">useUtils</strong> functions entirely inside your client browser sandbox. When you encode, decode, sign, or parse tokens and keys, the computations are handled by local JavaScript and Web Crypto APIs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          2. No Server Transmission
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans pl-4">
          We do not transmit your data over the network. Your keys, claims, secrets, and configuration inputs are never sent to our servers or stored in any database. Your browser console network tab can be audited at any time to verify that zero external network calls are made during utility computations.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          3. Browser Storage
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans pl-4">
          To improve user experience, some tools may store your non-sensitive preferences (such as light or dark theme choices) locally inside your browser's <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-zinc-950 border border-zinc-800 text-zinc-300 rounded px-1.5 py-0.5">localStorage</code>. We never store sensitive credentials, secrets, or keys in local storage.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          4. Updates to This Policy
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans pl-4">
          As our toolset grows, we will continue to adhere to our strict client-side-only execution standard. Any updates to this policy will reflect this core architectural constraint.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Footer Info Box -->
      <div class="mt-4 p-5 bg-zinc-900/30 border border-border-hairline rounded-lg flex items-start gap-3.5">
        <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-accent-emerald shrink-0 mt-1"></div>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-zinc-200">Privacy Audit Tool:</strong> You can inspect our source code directly in our repository or view the network tab in your browser's Developer Tools to confirm that no server transmissions occur.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
